properties.name: UI Events
properties.description: The events used to handle user interaction with UI elements.

properties.name: dxclick
properties.description: Raised when the element is clicked.

properties.name: dxcontextmenu
properties.description: Raised when the right mouse button is clicked on the element or when the element is held during a specified time period.

properties.name: dxdblclick
properties.description: Raised when a user has performed a double click on the element.

properties.name: dxdrag
properties.description: Raised when the drag gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxdragend
properties.description: Raised when the drag gesture has been completed.

properties.name: dxdragenter
properties.description: Raised when a user moves the pointer into the element, provided that the drag gesture is being performed.

properties.name: dxdragleave
properties.description: Raised when a user moves the pointer out of the element, provided that the drag gesture is being performed.

properties.name: dxdragstart
properties.description: Raised when the drag gesture has been started.

properties.name: dxdrop
properties.description: Raised when dragged data has been dropped on the element.

properties.name: dxhold
properties.description: Raised when the element is being held during a specified time.

properties.name: dxhoverend
properties.description: Raised when the mouse pointer leaves the element.

properties.name: dxhoverstart
properties.description: Raised when the mouse pointer appears over the element.

properties.name: dxpinch
properties.description: Raised when the pinch gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxpinchend
properties.description: Raised when the pinch gesture has been completed.

properties.name: dxpinchstart
properties.description: Raised when the pinch gesture has been started.

properties.name: dxpointercancel
properties.description: Raised when the browser decides that the pointer is unlikely to produce any more events.

properties.name: dxpointerdown
properties.description: Raised when the pointer takes on the active buttons state.

properties.name: dxpointerenter
properties.description: Raised when a pointer is moved to either the hit test area of an element or one of its descendants.

properties.name: dxpointerleave
properties.description: Raised when a pointer is moved from either the hit test area of an element or one of its descendants.

properties.name: dxpointermove
properties.description: Raised when any pointer parameter has been changed. (Position, tilt, pressure, button state, or contact geometry).

properties.name: dxpointerout
properties.description: Raised when a pointer is moved from either the hit test area of an element or one of its descendants.

properties.name: dxpointerover
properties.description: Raised when a pointer is moved to the hit test area of an element or one of its descendants.

properties.name: dxpointerup
properties.description: Raised when the pointer loses the active buttons state.

properties.name: dxremove
properties.description: Raised when a UI component associated with an element is being removed from the DOM.

properties.name: dxrotate
properties.description: Raised when the rotate gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxrotateend
properties.description: Raised when the rotate gesture has been completed.

properties.name: dxrotatestart
properties.description: Raised when the rotate gesture has been started.

properties.name: dxswipe
properties.description: Raised when the swipe gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxswipeend
properties.description: Raised when the swipe gesture is finished.

properties.name: dxswipestart
properties.description: Raised when the swipe gesture is started.

properties.name: dxtransform
properties.description: Raised when the transform gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxtransformend
properties.description: Raised when the transform gesture has been completed.

properties.name: dxtransformstart
properties.description: Raised when the transform gesture has been started.

properties.name: dxtranslate
properties.description: Raised when the translate gesture has been performed.

properties.name: dxtranslateend
properties.description: Raised when the translate gesture has been completed.

properties.name: dxtranslatestart
properties.description: Raised when the translate gesture has been started.
